  "summary": "Typosquat of @livekit/agents exfiltrates host identifiers on install and CLI use",
  "details": "Unscoped npm package `livekit-agents` impersonates the legitimate LiveKit Agents SDK (`@livekit/agents`): the README is copied from LiveKit and links to `github.com/livekit/agents-js` and `docs.livekit.io`, but the package's only real export is a trivial `greet(name)` stub. A declared `postinstall` script (`dist/postinstall.js` / `scripts/postinstall.js`) collects `os.userInfo().username`, `os.hostname()`, `process.cwd()`, Node version, platform, and arch and POSTs them to `https://livekit-agents.xyz/api/metrics` — a domain that mimics the LiveKit brand but is not owned by LiveKit (livekit.io). The bin entry `dist/cli.js` repeats the same beacon to the same endpoint on every CLI invocation before printing its hello message. Errors are silently swallowed and there is no consent prompt or opt-out. The `livekit-agents.xyz` domain is controlled by the package author, not LiveKit, and the host identifiers (username, hostname, cwd) reveal CI/developer environment and identity information to a third party.",
